node.text:
Absolutely in love with how @thelzcompound shop is coming along. I was skeptical about the @bendpak lifts at an angle, but the shop flows so dang good and has so much workspace. New Cree lighting from @econolight really sealed the deal. (Swipe for before and after).

I was on the fence about using this bay as our shop, but I’m so pumped we did. Amazing seeing a vision like this come to life!
#lzmfg #lzcompound

20% off at @econolight with “ADAM20”

node.text:
Stumbled upon this going through my laptop. At the end of 2016 I sat down and made a list of short and long term goals. In a video I broke them down into actionable items since goals are a lot easier to reach when you have tasks or smaller steps you can start acting on. Knowing where I’m at now, you may laugh at these “goals”. Reading this - hopefully you’ll realize that although your goals may seem far out of reach now - if you start doing what you can to get one step closer - you’ll reach them before you know it. If you aren’t actively doing SOMETHING to get where you want to be - it’s never going to just happen. Every little thing you do to get there matters - and its never too late to start. 

Sometimes people will ask “How crazy was it when you blew up” - and I’ll usually chuckle to myself and nod. Y’all OG’s know how long I’ve been at this. It’s been slow and steady growth for well over 10 years now and although it may not be an overnight success story, I’m almost more proud that I’ve been able to keep chasing my dreams for this long. The best part of it all is seeing how many of you guys stuck along for the ride. I am unbelievably appreciative and in awe of how many of you guys have been here since the BMX days, since the e46 days, since the college days, since the S13 days - no matter when you joined the journey - not one day of your support has been taken for granted. I can only hope that seeing me chase my dreams inspires you to chase your own. 

If you guys could do ONE thing for me and share something you did to reach your goals, or something you accomplished that might inspire others - please do. Reading your comment could be the little push someone needs to get out there and chase their dreams. ❤️

node.text:
Car is feeling better than ever here in Seattle! 9200rpm on this bank is music to my ears - upper mid tier qualifying run - kept it composed and I’m pumped! ❤️ @nittotire @bcracingna @garrettmotion @ecumasterusa @deatschwerks @designenginc @griotsgarage @yashiofactory @runbc @rayswheelsusa @bride_japan
@aemintakes @spectuned @drift.hq

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Adam LZed on July 28, 2021 tagging @drift.hq, and @duarte.hq. May be an image of car and outdoors.

node.text:
There is something @duarte.hq and I both share with these two cars. They mean the world to us - and were both monumental steps to get where we are today. I’ve had the pleasure of watching from the sidelines as Duarte and his team have grown @drift.hq into what it is today - helping countless people along the way. I am proud to announce that I am the new owner of @drift.hq, but even more stoked to have Duarte as a partner and his killer team. They care so much about drivers and drifting as a whole and have done an amazing job at creating a company that reflects that. I’m beyond excited to see how we can continue to push the limits together and put bring some of our wildest ideas to reality. 2021 may be halfway over… but it’s just getting started for us! 

I just uploaded a video talking about the thought process, back story, and some ideas that we have to continue improving as a company and helping more of you guys. Check it out now via the link in my bio. #LZMFG #DRIFTHQ

node.text: Opportunity of a lifetime! @311rsmotorsport and @porschemotorsportnorthamerica tossed me the keys to their 992 cup car here at BIR to turn some laps! Always dreamed of driving a Porsche racecar … let alone the latest and greatest! Carrera cup is here in the USA for the first time ever and 23 of these factory racecars battle head to head! This car is 1 of 2 that @311rs runs - driven by @lehmank and @ryangates . Can’t wait for you guys to see the video!
